SIMPLE: scissel
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Scissel
<hw>Scis"sel</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf.
<er>Scissile</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The clippings of metals made
in various mechanical operations.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The slips or plates of metal out of which circular
blanks have been cut for the purpose of coinage.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scissible</ent>⟦br⟧
